data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree building code **won't compile**. The new overload accepts a regular lambda, so conditional setters become trivial:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Parameter` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö names are now **uniquified** and nested paths are **fully qualified**

Two sub-changes:

- **Duplicate names get a numeric suffix.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` no longer silently share one column ŌĆö EF will append `1` to one of them.
- **Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of `BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** pin existing column names explicitly so migrations don't try to rename them:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types ŌĆö pin the old (short) name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");   // was auto-generated before
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) gained a `string logCommandText` parameter at the end. Your custom logger won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL sent to the DB
    }
}
```

Update **all** method signatures on that interface ŌĆö they all got the same new parameter.
